189
00:12:54,360 --> 00:12:56,480
直至吉姆・万斯的骚动平息
till this ruckus with Jim Vance blows over.

190
00:12:56,730 --> 00:12:58,410
你最好就喝死在那里
You'll drink yourself to death up there.

191
00:12:58,660 --> 00:13:01,080
我不是去赴死的
I ain't going up there to die.

192
00:13:01,710 --> 00:13:03,890
我是为了好好活着
I'm going up there to stay alive.

193
00:13:04,140 --> 00:13:05,560
你错了
Ain't right.

194
00:13:05,810 --> 00:13:07,360
从军队回来以后
Come home from the army,

195
00:13:07,610 --> 00:13:09,030
把我当奶牛一样就知道让我生
breedin' me like I was cattle,

196
00:13:09,280 --> 00:13:11,260
你现在又想一走了之吗?
then you take off again?

197
00:13:11,510 --> 00:13:14,710
你难道忘记自己丈夫和父亲的职责了吗?
No, you've got your duties as a husband and father.

198
00:13:16,820 --> 00:13:18,530
孩子们 我不在家你们要照顾好妈妈
Kids, mind your mama while I'm gone.

199
00:13:18,780 --> 00:13:20,620
我们会的
We will.

200
00:14:23,580 --> 00:14:24,330
莉瓦西
Levicy.

201
00:14:26,020 --> 00:14:27,460
安德森?
Anderson?

202
00:14:39,400 --> 00:14:40,600
我受够了战争
I'm done with the war.

203
00:14:50,910 --> 00:14:52,130
你再也不回去了吗?
You ain't going back?

204
00:14:52,380 --> 00:14:53,410
我已经受够了
I've given enough.

205
00:14:56,280 --> 00:14:57,600
亲爱的 我平安回来了
I'm back for good, darling.

206
00:14:57,850 --> 00:15:02,000
上帝保佑 你平安回来了
Lord, you lived through it.

207
00:15:02,250 --> 00:15:03,830
我们的孩子怎么样?
How's our little boy?

208
00:15:04,460 --> 00:15:09,110
我们的小天使入睡了
He's an angel now that he's asleep.

209
00:15:10,400 --> 00:15:13,220
天哪 看看你
oh, my god, look at you.

210
00:15:13,470 --> 00:15:14,880
有件事你一定得知道
You'll want to know

211
00:15:15,130 --> 00:15:16,850
去年我们收了至少六十蒲式耳的玉米
that we got at least 60 bushels of corn in last year,

212
00:15:17,100 --> 00:15:18,550
我们没有挨饿
so we ain't starvin',

213
00:15:18,800 --> 00:15:20,490
今年的收成也会很不错
and this year promises to be just as good,

214
00:15:20,740 --> 00:15:21,820
所以你不用操心
so you don't have to worry none,

215
00:15:22,070 --> 00:15:24,040
约翰斯 还有 你绝对认不...
and johnse, you will not recog...

216
00:15:28,480 --> 00:15:30,580
我们明早再说
We'll get to all that come morning.

217
00:15:45,480 --> 00:15:48,980
西弗吉尼亚州 垂山

218
00:15:59,540 --> 00:16:00,950
嘿!
Hey!

219
00:16:04,950 --> 00:16:09,300
那不是玛莎・麦考伊吗?
Ain't that martha McCoy?

220
00:16:09,550 --> 00:16:10,900
利亚斯替一下
'Lias.

221
00:16:26,410 --> 00:16:27,960
麦考伊夫人
Miss McCoy.

222
00:16:28,210 --> 00:16:31,990
你应该听说了我家哈蒙的情况
Suppose you heard about my harmon.

223
00:16:32,240 --> 00:16:36,330
他在酿酒场待了一个多月 饮酒度日
He's up at that still over a month, drinking.

224
00:16:36,580 --> 00:16:38,390
说万一他现在收手
Says if'n he stops now,

225
00:16:38,640 --> 00:16:39,700
当吉姆・万斯杀上门的时候
he'll throw a fit and be helpless

226
00:16:39,950 --> 00:16:42,940
他将既愤怒又无助
when Jim Vance come to kill him.

227
00:16:43,190 --> 00:16:44,540
女士 不只是对我的吉姆叔叔来说
Ma'am, your yankee husband was a traitor

228
00:16:44,790 --> 00:16:48,840
你的北方丈夫是个叛徒
to more than just my uncle jim.

229
00:16:49,090 --> 00:16:50,510
在这的许多弟兄
There's lots of folks around here

230
00:16:50,760 --> 00:16:53,220
都无法宽恕哈蒙的背叛行经 或许...
can't forgive harmon's betrayal and might...

231
00:16:53,470 --> 00:16:55,420
或许他们也很想取他性命
Might want to kill him,

232
00:16:55,670 --> 00:16:57,360
其中不乏有你的一些亲戚
even some of your own kin.

233
00:16:57,610 --> 00:17:01,760
但哈蒙就只指控了你的吉姆・万斯叔叔
But your uncle Jim Vance is the only one my harmon accused

234
00:17:02,010 --> 00:17:05,630
和他的猎狗通奸
of fornicating with his hound dog.

235
00:17:05,880 --> 00:17:08,160
这个...
Well...

236
00:17:08,410 --> 00:17:10,600
这真是低劣的用词
That's a poor choice of words.

237
00:17:10,850 --> 00:17:15,510
找个藏身之所确实是明智的行为
I'll admit, hidin' out was prudent.

238
00:17:15,950 --> 00:17:19,510
我不想变成一个寡妇苟活
I can't survive being a widow.

239
00:17:25,860 --> 00:17:29,380
我叔叔总是我行我素
My uncle tends to go his own way.

240
00:17:29,630 --> 00:17:32,250
但下次我见到他
But next time I see him,

241
00:17:33,020 --> 00:17:34,340
我会尽力相劝
i'll do what I can.

242
00:17:40,650 --> 00:17:43,780
南茜 坐下
Nancy, sit down.

243
00:18:42,610 --> 00:18:45,760
我知道你在这!
I hear ya!

244
00:18:46,010 --> 00:18:50,710
你抓不住我的 你这狗崽子!
Ya ain't getting me, you son of a bitch!

245
00:19:46,160 --> 00:19:48,410
爸爸?
Pappy?

246
00:19:48,660 --> 00:19:50,530
爸爸?
Pappy?

247
00:19:51,680 --> 00:19:52,700
爸爸?
Pappy?

248
00:19:55,700 --> 00:19:58,260
"亲爱的兰德尔"
"Dear Randall,"

249
00:19:58,510 --> 00:20:01,420
"时运艰难"
"our fortunes are bitter."

250
00:20:01,670 --> 00:20:05,470
"哈特菲尔德传话说"
"Your brother harmon was done murdered,"

251
00:20:05,720 --> 00:20:08,410
"你的弟弟哈蒙被谋杀了"
"it is said by Hatfields.

252
00:20:08,660 --> 00:20:12,820
"我们也只能勉强度日"
"The rest of us barely scrape by."

253
00:20:13,070 --> 00:20:16,690
"亲爱的丈夫 如果你还活着"
"If you are still alive, dear husband,"

254
00:20:16,940 --> 00:20:21,830
"愿你速归"
"i pray that you come home to us soon."

255
00:20:22,080 --> 00:20:25,480
"爱妻 莎莉"
"Your loving wife, sally."

256
00:20:30,350 --> 00:20:31,280
结束了!
It's over!

257
00:20:31,530 --> 00:20:34,120
战争结束了!
The war is over!

258
00:20:35,230 --> 00:20:36,380
李将军属南方邦联

259
00:20:35,230 --> 00:20:36,380
李将军投降了!
General lee surrendered!

260
00:20:36,630 --> 00:20:37,910
- 上帝保佑! - 这场战争终于结束了!
- Praise the lord! - The war is over!

261
00:20:38,160 --> 00:20:40,010
感谢上帝 感谢耶稣
Thank you, thank you, jesus.

262
00:20:40,260 --> 00:20:41,460
真见鬼
Now, I'll be damned.

263
00:20:48,810 --> 00:20:52,530
对某些人来说战争永不休止
Won't be over for some.

264
00:20:52,780 --> 00:20:57,460
战争真他妈是一种浪费
War was a goddamn waste.

265
00:20:57,710 --> 00:21:00,080
我可不想让和平成为战争的祭品
I don't intend to waste the peace.

266
00:21:41,710 --> 00:21:45,080
肯塔基州

267
00:22:10,820 --> 00:22:14,040
谁?
Who's there?

268
00:22:14,290 --> 00:22:16,130
转过来
Now turn around.

269
00:22:21,600 --> 00:22:23,060
兰德尔?
Randall?

270
00:22:25,940 --> 00:22:29,060
莎莉 是我
Sally, it's me.

271
00:22:29,310 --> 00:22:31,560
你憔悴了不少
You've aged some.

272
00:22:31,810 --> 00:22:34,060
北方佬干的
Yankees done it.

273
00:22:34,310 --> 00:22:37,740
在监狱里我们简直是猪狗不如
Treated us worse than animals in that prison.

274
00:22:42,620 --> 00:22:45,500
我并非打算放弃你 我的丈夫 但我别无选择
I didn't want to give up on you, husband, but I think I did.

275
00:22:51,860 --> 00:22:54,310
首先 从我这片林子里砍十英亩树...
First we log my ten acres here...

276
00:22:54,760 --> 00:22:59,760
越过山脊直至丘陵后背
Run from the ridge across and outside that hill.

277
00:23:00,370 --> 00:23:02,090
然后呢?
Then?

278
00:23:02,340 --> 00:23:03,520
我们从中获利
We take the money from that.

279
00:23:03,770 --> 00:23:06,060
就可以再买二十英亩的地
We buy 20 more acres.

280
00:23:06,310 --> 00:23:08,630
买完地呢?
Then what?

281
00:23:08,880 --> 00:23:10,180
再买四十英亩
Buy 40 more.

282
00:23:14,420 --> 00:23:16,600
这就像用马车轮擦你的屁股一样
It's like wiping your ass with a wagon wheel.

283
00:23:16,850 --> 00:23:18,390
没完没了的?
Ain't never gonna end now, is it?

284
00:23:19,420 --> 00:23:21,740
哈特菲尔德先生
Mr. Hatfield.

285
00:23:21,990 --> 00:23:24,910
我是兰德尔・麦考伊的表弟兼律师
I'm a cousin of randall McCoy, an attorney.

286
00:23:25,160 --> 00:23:30,120
我叫佩里・克莱因
My name is Perry Cline.

287
00:23:30,470 --> 00:23:32,310
我在路易维耳市的
I studied law at the offices

288
00:23:32,310 --> 00:23:35,300
伊桑・麦基宾办事处学习法律
of ethan mckibbin in louisville.

289
00:23:35,550 --> 00:23:38,790
去年十月通过了律师考核
Passed the bar last october.

290
00:23:39,040 --> 00:23:41,850
我对即将造成的不快…
I apologize for any unpleasantness

291
00:23:42,100 --> 00:23:43,260
提前致歉
we're about to have.

292
00:23:43,510 --> 00:23:46,070
克莱因先生 有话直说
Just state your business, mr. Cline.

293
00:23:46,320 --> 00:23:47,700
我知道你自认为
Now, I know you believe

294
00:23:47,950 --> 00:23:49,700
自己拥有这片林地
you own this stand of timber

295
00:23:49,950 --> 00:23:53,040
并有权利进行砍伐
and have the right to cut.

296
00:23:53,890 --> 00:23:58,850
然而依据相关法律规定 并非如此
Whereas, in fact, in the eyes of the law, you do not.

297
00:23:59,400 --> 00:24:01,680
你的想法究竟从何而来?
Where in thunder did you get that?

298
00:24:01,930 --> 00:24:05,010
这林地是我老爹1859年
My daddy bought this parcel

299
00:24:05,010 --> 00:24:07,580
从一个越南佬手里买的
off of bucky hand in 1859.

300
00:24:07,830 --> 00:24:09,460
那份契约还躺在家里的一个盒子里呢
I got the deed in a box at home.

301
00:24:09,710 --> 00:24:12,760
我当然相信你 哈特菲尔德先生
I believe you, Mr. Hatfield.

302
00:24:13,010 --> 00:24:14,730
但他把这木材卖给了我的表兄拉瑟福德
But he sold my cousin Rutherford,

303
00:24:14,980 --> 00:24:17,400
现在由我来打理他的财产
whose estate I administer,

304
00:24:17,950 --> 00:24:22,940
早在1858年6月22日就获得木材采伐权
the timber rights beforehand on june 22, 1858.

305
00:24:23,650 --> 00:24:27,810
签字并得以见证 瞧?
Signed and witnessed, see?

306
00:24:28,060 --> 00:24:29,810
那越南佬是我家的一个朋友
Well, bucky was a friend of my family.

307
00:24:30,060 --> 00:24:32,830
如果我们只买了地没买木材 
He'd have told us

308
00:24:32,830 --> 00:24:34,750
他不会不告诉我们的
if we'd not bought the timber with the land.

309
00:24:35,000 --> 00:24:38,910
你这是在逼我起诉 哈特菲尔德先生
You'll force me to sue, mr. Hatfield.

310
00:24:39,160 --> 00:24:42,120
你得承担所有的损失
You'll be liable for damages

311
00:24:42,440 --> 00:24:45,330
还需要支付迄今为止你所砍伐的所有木材
and the cost of all my timber you have cut to date.

312
00:24:45,580 --> 00:24:46,580
你输定了
You will lose.

313
00:24:46,830 --> 00:24:51,130
那是威胁吗?
That a threat?

314
00:24:51,380 --> 00:24:54,510
我想你还是去起诉更安全
I reckon it's safer you sue.

315
00:24:54,760 --> 00:24:57,470
在没有听到法官异词之前
Without they hear different from a judge,

316
00:24:57,820 --> 00:25:02,810
我的亲戚会以为你在试图敲诈
my relatives might think you just tried to bamboozle me.

317
00:25:03,460 --> 00:25:05,350
那好吧...
Well...

318
00:25:05,600 --> 00:25:08,750
我已表明自己的权利
I've informed you of my rights.

319
00:25:09,480 --> 00:25:13,350
且看法律如何裁决
We'll see what the law has to say about it.

320
00:25:13,600 --> 00:25:14,870
祝你愉快
I bid you good day.

321
00:25:43,430 --> 00:25:48,190
我已准备好尽妻职责
I'm prepared to do my duty as your wife,

322
00:25:48,440 --> 00:25:53,060
但我请求把种子播在我体外
but I ask that you spill your seed outside of me.

323
00:25:53,310 --> 00:25:55,400
我难以承受再育一儿
I could not bear another birth.

324
00:26:31,610 --> 00:26:34,770
? 我主为何流出宝血 ?
Alas and did my savior bleed

325
00:26:35,020 --> 00:26:39,470
? 愿意忍受死亡 ?
and did my sovereign die

326
00:26:39,720 --> 00:26:41,910
? 甘愿代替 ?
would he devote

327
00:26:42,160 --> 00:26:44,510
? 卑微的我 ?
the sacred head

328
00:26:44,760 --> 00:26:49,200
? 遍历痛苦悲怆 ?
for such a worm as I

329
00:26:49,450 --> 00:26:52,350
? 借我主十字架 ?
at the cross, at the cross

330
00:26:52,600 --> 00:26:54,790
? 我得见主恩光 ?
where I first saw the light

331
00:26:55,040 --> 00:26:57,420
? 除罪恶重担 ?
and the burdens of my heart

332
00:26:57,670 --> 00:26:59,630
? 我心洁净 ?
rolled away

333
00:27:00,210 --> 00:27:02,600
? 借十架我信仰 ?
it was there by faith

334
00:27:02,850 --> 00:27:05,300
? 眼明亮心平康 ?
I received my sight

335
00:27:05,550 --> 00:27:07,530
? 到如今 不分昼夜 ?
and now I am happy

336
00:27:07,780 --> 00:27:10,060
? 快乐欢畅 ?
all the day

337
00:27:10,620 --> 00:27:15,580
? 我主为何流出宝血 ?
alas and did my savior bleed

338
00:27:15,830 --> 00:27:20,650
? 为何忍受死亡 ?
and did my sovereign die

339
00:27:20,900 --> 00:27:23,360
? 甘愿代替 ?
would he devote

340
00:27:35,080 --> 00:27:36,700
保重
Well, then, take care.

341
00:27:36,950 --> 00:27:38,230
很高兴再次见到你
Now, good see you again.

342
00:27:38,480 --> 00:27:39,900
很高兴见到你
Nice to see you.

343
00:27:40,150 --> 00:27:43,400
兰德尔 很高兴见到你
Randall, good to see you.

344
00:27:43,650 --> 00:27:45,540
多多保重 谢谢您的到来
Now, take care. Thank you so much.

345
00:27:45,790 --> 00:27:47,790
兰德尔!
Randall!

346
00:27:49,960 --> 00:27:54,640
兰德尔!
Randall!

347
00:27:54,890 --> 00:27:57,820
别闹了
Oh, now, stop fighting.

348
00:27:58,070 --> 00:28:00,250
莎莉
Sally.

349
00:28:00,500 --> 00:28:01,890
莎莉 我们聊聊吧
Sally, you come talk with me.

350
00:28:02,140 --> 00:28:02,920
约翰斯 过来
Come on, Johnse.

351
00:28:03,170 --> 00:28:04,320
来
Come on.

352
00:28:04,570 --> 00:28:06,410
快来
Come on now.

353
00:28:09,040 --> 00:28:11,780
没想到你会在耶和华殿里
Hard to reconcile you in the lord's house.

354
00:28:13,320 --> 00:28:17,870
莉瓦西硬拖我来的...
Yeah, well, Levicy dragged me here to...

355
00:28:18,120 --> 00:28:20,670
真的很高兴见到你 兰德尔
It's good to see you, Randall.

356
00:28:20,920 --> 00:28:25,280
我担心...担心你死在了战场上
I feared...feared you dead.

357
00:28:25,530 --> 00:28:29,680
很多次我都觉得我已经死了
Times I felt like I was.

358
00:28:30,090 --> 00:28:35,090
剩下的兄弟们...或死或失踪 只剩我一个
Rest of the company...all lost, all dead, except me.

359
00:28:35,940 --> 00:28:37,890
莎莉 我们的丈夫都回来了
Our men are home now, sally.

360
00:28:38,140 --> 00:28:39,660
你的是回来了
Yours is.

361
00:28:39,910 --> 00:28:44,800
我丈夫似乎只回来了一半
Mine is only half home.

362
00:28:45,050 --> 00:28:46,530
我说选举那天来看看吧
I mean to enter the election day contest,

363
00:28:46,780 --> 00:28:50,740
当然我尊重你的选择
and I would value your opinion.

364
00:28:50,990 --> 00:28:52,610
拿着
Go ahead.

365
00:28:52,860 --> 00:28:54,310
接骨木果酱?
Elderberry?

366
00:28:54,560 --> 00:28:55,830
没有比这更甜的了
There's nothing sweeter.

367
00:28:56,080 --> 00:28:57,840
不堪设想你都经历了些什么...
It's terrible bad what happened to you...

368
00:28:58,090 --> 00:29:01,850
监狱和所有的一切
Prison and all.

369
00:29:02,100 --> 00:29:03,720
如果有什么可以帮忙的地方
If there's anything I can do to help out.

370
00:29:04,370 --> 00:29:09,320
你是在为你的背叛寻求良心安慰吗?
You propose now to ease your conscience for deserting?

371
00:29:09,770 --> 00:29:12,930
还是为我弟弟的死?
Or for my brother's murder?

372
00:29:13,180 --> 00:29:14,960
是你那个吉姆叔叔干的
Your uncle Jim done it.

373
00:29:15,210 --> 00:29:19,470
如果他在这 我会当面质问
If'n he was here, i'd say it to his face.

374
00:29:19,720 --> 00:29:22,150
吉姆发誓他跟哈蒙的死无关
Jim swears he had nothing to do with harmon's death.

375
00:29:22,400 --> 00:29:24,120
你居然买他的账?
And you believe that?

376
00:29:29,120 --> 00:29:31,580
我不懂与人争执 兰德尔
Well, I have no knowledge to the contrary, randall.

377
00:29:31,830 --> 00:29:36,820
况且吉姆叔叔他...他在上帝面前发了誓的
And uncle jim, he...He swore before god.

378
00:29:37,170 --> 00:29:41,420
哈特菲尔德家族的人要上帝有什么用?
And what use do Hatfields have of god?

379
00:29:44,500 --> 00:29:46,360
就这么说定了 你拿着 尝尝
Well, you keep that, and you try it.

380
00:29:46,610 --> 00:29:47,630
如果这做得...
Let me know if'n it set up and...

381
00:29:47,880 --> 00:29:49,110
谢谢
Thank you.

382
00:29:52,280 --> 00:29:53,210
我不明白...
I don't understa...

383
00:30:02,680 --> 00:30:05,210
太平绅士 瓦伦丁・哈特菲尔德

384
00:30:13,490 --> 00:30:15,020
早安
Mornin'.

385
00:30:15,270 --> 00:30:17,040
我要给你看样东西 克莱因先生
There's something I'd like to show you, Mr. Cline.

386
00:30:17,290 --> 00:30:18,820
差不多要开庭了
Court's about to convene.

387
00:30:19,070 --> 00:30:22,260
是的 我知道 我想你会很期待这东西的
Yeah, well, I think you'll wait for this.

388
00:30:22,510 --> 00:30:24,250
艾利生・利亚斯 
Ellison, 'lias,

389
00:30:24,250 --> 00:30:27,080
给克莱因律师看看我们的证据
show lawyer cline our evidence.

390
00:30:32,130 --> 00:30:36,140
你说哈米什1859年为你那张契约作了见证
You recall that hamish was witness on your bill of sale

391
00:30:36,390 --> 00:30:41,010
但原来发现他
in '59 but somehow died,

392
00:30:41,520 --> 00:30:43,210
早在1857年时就入土了
got himself buried in '57.

393
00:30:43,810 --> 00:30:47,070
有印象吗?
You recall that?

394
00:30:50,440 --> 00:30:51,990
我怎么就被假证给耍了
I am somehow made a victim of a fraud.

395
00:30:52,240 --> 00:30:53,790
也不知道我怎么就...
How is not clear to me...

396
00:30:54,040 --> 00:30:56,790
或许你应该跟法官好好解释一下
Maybe you oughta should just fetch the sheriff.

397
00:30:57,040 --> 00:30:58,790
也许他可以帮你缉拿那个
Perchance he can help you track down the scoundrel

398
00:30:59,040 --> 00:31:01,290
把你骗得团团转的骗子
what sold you a bill of goods.

399
00:31:01,540 --> 00:31:03,930
显然这是个变数 哈特菲尔德先生
Obviously this changes things, mr. Hatfield.

400
00:31:04,180 --> 00:31:05,470
是啊
Yeah.

401
00:31:05,720 --> 00:31:07,370
我撤诉
I forgo.

402
00:31:07,620 --> 00:31:10,870
我放弃索取在你土地上的砍伐权
I abandon and renounce claim to the timber rights on your land,

403
00:31:11,120 --> 00:31:13,340
并为我的草率感到抱歉
and I apologize for being hasty

404
00:31:13,590 --> 00:31:17,100
并提出了一起无效的索赔
and putting forth an invalid claim.

405
00:31:17,350 --> 00:31:19,220
你应该得到赔偿 必须的
You deserve to be compensated. You shall be.

406
00:31:19,470 --> 00:31:20,560
我身上有二十二美元
I have $22 here.

407
00:31:20,810 --> 00:31:24,150
把你的钱收起来
Keep your money.

408
00:31:24,400 --> 00:31:27,420
我别无它意 哈特菲尔德先生
I take that kindly, mr. Hatfield.

409
00:31:27,670 --> 00:31:29,020
事业刚起步的年轻律师
Young lawyer starting his career,

410
00:31:29,410 --> 00:31:34,000
轻易就被一份伪造证件给耍了 形势不妙啊
deceived by a forged document don't look well.

411
00:31:34,250 --> 00:31:36,270
太不妙了
Don't look well at all.

412
00:31:36,520 --> 00:31:38,370
人们甚至不禁会开始猜想
People might even start to think

413
00:31:38,620 --> 00:31:43,580
你从中也掺了一脚 并搞得一团糟
that you had a hand in this forgin' and then bungled it.

414
00:31:46,430 --> 00:31:50,550
你想干嘛 哈特菲尔德先生
What do you want, mr. Hatfield?

415
00:31:50,800 --> 00:31:54,250
你想要得到所有属于我的东西
Well, you meant to have all that was mine.

416
00:31:54,500 --> 00:31:57,090
所以我也要得到你的一切
So I must be entitled to have all what's yours.

417
00:31:59,470 --> 00:32:04,390
至少是你从你父亲那继承的部分
At least what you inherited from your daddy.

418
00:32:05,040 --> 00:32:08,130
那可是五千亩地啊
That's 5,000 acres.

419
00:32:08,380 --> 00:32:12,200
我不贪图你的林地
Don't hardly much want the land.

420
00:32:12,450 --> 00:32:14,390
我只要伐木权
Just the timber rights.

421
00:32:20,120 --> 00:32:24,350
我想我们没必要闹到法庭上 是吧?
I don't believe we have to go in court at all, do we?

422
00:32:24,600 --> 00:32:26,520
找不到 老爹
Can't find her, pa.

423
00:32:26,770 --> 00:32:28,450
该死的
Consarn it.

424
00:32:28,700 --> 00:32:30,490
继续找
Keep looking.

425
00:32:30,740 --> 00:32:32,450
只是一只小猪而已
It's one little pig.

426
00:32:32,700 --> 00:32:34,890
而且很可能被山狮吃了
Mountain lion probably got her.

427
00:32:35,140 --> 00:32:37,860
那只猪如果养肥了可以够我们吃一个冬天
That pig fattened up feeds this family for a whole winter.

428
00:32:38,110 --> 00:32:40,140
明白吗 孩子?
You understand that, boy?

429
00:32:43,220 --> 00:32:46,100
灾难折磨着我们
Misfortune afflicts us both.

430
00:32:46,620 --> 00:32:48,770
抱歉让你失去了林地 表弟 
Sorry about you losing your land, cousin.

431
00:32:49,620 --> 00:32:53,580
但是 他们的背信弃义改变不了
Still, we cannot let our paths be diverted

432
00:32:53,830 --> 00:32:55,360
我们的原则
by the treachery of others.

433
00:32:55,610 --> 00:32:57,900
相信上帝 多做善事
Trust in the lord and do good,

434
00:32:58,730 --> 00:33:01,530
你就会得偿所愿
and he shall give thee the desires of thine heart.

435
00:33:01,780 --> 00:33:04,070
完成了 爸爸 你喜欢吗?
All done, poppy. You like it?

436
00:33:08,170 --> 00:33:11,190
剪得很好 罗斯安娜
Fine job, roseanna.

437
00:33:11,440 --> 00:33:14,090
给
Here.

438
00:33:14,340 --> 00:33:15,330
我一直想把这个给你
I've been meaning to give you this.

439
00:33:15,580 --> 00:33:16,470
金纽扣?
A gold button?

440
00:33:16,720 --> 00:33:17,830
这是战争中得到的
It's from the war.

441
00:33:18,080 --> 00:33:19,170
给我吗?
For me?

442
00:33:19,420 --> 00:33:23,270
因为你是我的最爱
'Cause you're my favorite.

443
00:33:23,520 --> 00:33:25,540
或许你是对的 兰德尔
Perhaps you're right, randall.

444
00:33:26,220 --> 00:33:28,410
但我不会放松警惕
But I would not drop my guard.

445
00:33:29,020 --> 00:33:31,250
战争改造了人
War changes men.

446
00:33:31,500 --> 00:33:32,580
到了和平时期 他们就变成
Peacetime can turn them into

447
00:33:32,830 --> 00:33:35,380
诡计多端的蛇
scheming snakes.

448
00:33:35,630 --> 00:33:37,690
我猜哈特菲尔德会不停地来找你
I predict Hatfield will keep coming at you

449
00:33:37,940 --> 00:33:42,620
假装友好而慷慨
feigning friendship and generosity.

450
00:33:42,870 --> 00:33:44,930
当他这么做时
And when he does,

451
00:33:45,450 --> 00:33:47,710
你就会知道我是对的
you'll know I'm right.

452
00:33:59,920 --> 00:34:04,880
我就觉得会在这找到你 兰德尔
I hoped I might find you here, randall.

453
00:34:05,830 --> 00:34:08,630
就像从前一样 对吧?
Almost like old times, huh?

454
00:34:12,200 --> 00:34:15,160
什么风把你吹到城镇来了?
What brings you to town?

455
00:34:15,410 --> 00:34:17,530
生意
Business.

456
00:34:17,780 --> 00:34:19,300
我刚刚和金克斯・克莱布瑞特达成协议
I just made a deal with jinx clabberat

457
00:34:19,550 --> 00:34:22,530
将他的一些部分好的低洼地转让给我的人
to farm out some of his good bottomland with my boys.

458
00:34:22,780 --> 00:34:26,200
我们可以种一些经济作物
We might just grow us a big cash crop of tobaccy.

459
00:34:26,450 --> 00:34:27,450
很好
Good.

460
00:34:28,150 --> 00:34:29,470
很好
Good.

461
00:34:29,720 --> 00:34:31,010
你是来这炫耀
You come to boast about stealing

462
00:34:31,560 --> 00:34:36,480
从我表弟佩里・克莱因那里夺来的成果吗?
from my cousin Perry Cline?

463
00:34:37,030 --> 00:34:38,450
没有人来这炫耀 兰德尔
Nobody come here to boast, randall.

464
00:34:38,700 --> 00:34:42,470
我只是想向你示好
I'm just-i'm just trying to be friendly.

465
00:34:46,740 --> 00:34:48,190
我不知道你听说了什么
I don't know what you heard,

466
00:34:48,540 --> 00:34:53,500
但我没有一样东西是从你表弟那夺来的
but nary a thing was stole from your kin.

467
00:34:53,850 --> 00:34:55,560
当我揭穿佩里・克莱因的谎言时
Perry Cline gave me his timber rights

468
00:34:55,810 --> 00:35:00,100
他就把伐木权给了我
when I uncovered how he was trying to cheat me.

469
00:35:00,350 --> 00:35:02,200
我当时就该打爆他该死的脑袋
I should've blown his damn head off is what I shoulda done,

470
00:35:02,450 --> 00:35:03,490
但是...
but...

471
00:35:07,530 --> 00:35:09,370
你认为我这是阴谋诡计 你..
You think I profited unfairly, you...

472
00:35:12,230 --> 00:35:14,080
你拿着这个
you take this.

473
00:35:14,330 --> 00:35:19,260
你凭良心收下
You take that in good conscience.

474
00:35:19,610 --> 00:35:21,490
这是不是让你饱受折磨呀?
Does it weigh on you at all, captain Hatfield,

475
00:35:21,740 --> 00:35:23,290
你轻松获利 而其他人坚持到底
how you profited while others stayed the course

476
00:35:23,540 --> 00:35:26,310
却受苦受难?
and suffered for it?

477
00:35:30,280 --> 00:35:34,040
没有人能质疑我付出 了多少
No man questions what I gave the cause, randall.

478
00:35:34,290 --> 00:35:35,650
尤其是你
Especially you.

479
00:35:56,280 --> 00:35:58,110
再来一杯
'nother one.

480
00:36:00,280 --> 00:36:04,110
1878年
西弗吉尼亚州 拖轮河谷

481
00:36:08,920 --> 00:36:12,840
传言说 这里要建一条铁路
Talk is, they're gonna build a railroad right through here.

482
00:36:13,090 --> 00:36:15,640
那样我们的木材就可以运往各个地方
Then we'll send our timber in all directions

483
00:36:15,890 --> 00:36:17,310
遍及全国
'round the whole country.

484
00:36:17,560 --> 00:36:19,680
我希望不要运往北方
Not up north, I hope.

485
00:36:19,930 --> 00:36:21,020
战争早就结束了
War's long over, jim.

486
00:36:21,270 --> 00:36:22,720
没有南北之分
There's no north, no south-

487
00:36:22,970 --> 00:36:25,850
只有赚钱的人和不赚钱的人
Just people who got money and people who ain't.

488
00:36:26,100 --> 00:36:28,820
我打算和他们做生意
I mean to do business with them that has.

489
00:36:29,070 --> 00:36:30,460
我一直都坚信我们会发财
I always knew we was gonna be rich.

490
00:36:30,710 --> 00:36:33,660
嘿!
Hey!

491
00:36:33,910 --> 00:36:36,100
威廉 你的孩子!
It's your boy, william!

492
00:36:36,350 --> 00:36:37,670
树倒了!
Tree fell!

493
00:36:38,290 --> 00:36:41,770
木渣掉进了他的眼睛!
Splinter caught his eye!

494
00:36:42,020 --> 00:36:45,390
我看不到!
I can't see!

495
00:36:46,590 --> 00:36:49,740
埃迪 我什么也看不到!
Eddie, I can't see!

496
00:36:49,990 --> 00:36:51,280
为什么我看不见?
Why can't I see?

497
00:36:51,530 --> 00:36:54,280
我知道很难受 孩子
I know it hurts bad, son.

498
00:36:54,530 --> 00:36:57,890
我很佩服你 佩服你能忍受这么大的痛苦
I admire how you-I admire how you standin' up to it.

499
00:36:58,440 --> 00:37:00,090
给我一些水
Give me some water.

500
00:37:00,340 --> 00:37:01,660
约翰斯 为什么我看不到?
Johnse, why can't I see?

501
00:37:01,910 --> 00:37:03,430
我们马上送你看医生
We're gonna get you to a doctor straightaway.

502
00:37:03,680 --> 00:37:06,800
昂斯
Anse.

503
00:37:07,050 --> 00:37:08,320
你不会死的
You're not gonna die,

504
00:37:08,980 --> 00:37:10,830
但我不想撒谎
but I won't lie to you.

505
00:37:11,080 --> 00:37:12,750
你伤得很重
This is a serious wound.

506
00:37:37,080 --> 00:37:39,430
你好 邻居
Howdy, neighbors.

507
00:37:39,680 --> 00:37:41,260
兰德尔
Randall.

508
00:37:41,510 --> 00:37:42,150
莎莉夫人
Miss sally.

509
00:37:42,480 --> 00:37:44,320
你还好吗 浮洛伊德?
How do you do, floyd?

510
00:37:48,750 --> 00:37:50,170
大好的日子 是吧?
Blessed day, ain't it?

511
00:37:50,420 --> 00:37:51,540
当然啦
Sure is.

512
00:37:51,790 --> 00:37:53,680
你这季收成如何?
How's your harvest this season?

513
00:37:53,930 --> 00:37:55,880
一般般
Fair to middlin'.

514
00:37:56,130 --> 00:37:57,180
比上不足
Better than the last one.

515
00:37:57,430 --> 00:37:59,630
比下有余
Not as good as the next.

516
00:38:00,770 --> 00:38:02,180
你的猪养得好肥
Your hogs fattened up nice.

517
00:38:02,430 --> 00:38:03,990
哦 坏脾气的小家伙
Ah, ornery critters.

518
00:38:04,240 --> 00:38:06,750
孩子们和狗试图圈住它们时
Had the kids and dogs try to round them up,

519
00:38:07,000 --> 00:38:10,390
它们就不停地哼哼
but these two kept a'squealin' off.

520
00:38:10,640 --> 00:38:11,660
告诉我 你养这个斑点猪
Tell me, floyd, how long have you had

521
00:38:11,910 --> 00:38:13,830
多长时间了?
that spotted shoat there?

522
00:38:14,080 --> 00:38:15,430
呃 去年的
Well, he bred last year.

523
00:38:15,970 --> 00:38:17,500
我知道它什么时候养的
I know when it was bred.

524
00:38:17,750 --> 00:38:20,350
我在它耳朵上做了记号
That's my markin' on its ears.

525
00:38:20,600 --> 00:38:23,710
哦 不 兰德尔 你弄错了
Ah, no, randall, you're mistook.

526
00:38:24,230 --> 00:38:27,110
我特意在我的猪上做了记号 
I notch my swines particular

527
00:38:27,110 --> 00:38:28,880
这样我就不会弄错
so I do not get mistook.

528
00:38:29,130 --> 00:38:31,580
呃 你知道的 小猪很喜欢到处跑
Well, you know young pigs is wanderers.

529
00:38:31,830 --> 00:38:34,520
我想我的一两头猪或许正挂在你的厨房里
I expect you gots one or two of mine hangin' in your smokehouse.

530
00:38:34,770 --> 00:38:36,820
我不会
I do not.

531
00:38:37,070 --> 00:38:38,920
你到底还偷了多少我的猪?
How many more of my pigs you took?

532
00:38:39,170 --> 00:38:42,000
你偷了多少我的猪肉来填饱你的肚皮?
How much pork you takin' from my family to stuff your belly?

533
00:38:42,250 --> 00:38:44,860
等会儿 兰德尔 这是个大罪名
Now, hang on, randall. That's a serious accusal.

534
00:38:45,110 --> 00:38:47,230
你是想吵架吧
You's bein' quarrelsome.

535
00:38:47,480 --> 00:38:48,760
我就是了 怎么样?
I am, am i?

536
00:38:49,010 --> 00:38:51,430
试试这个怎么样?
Well, how's this for quarrelsome?

537
00:38:52,060 --> 00:38:57,060
该死的偷猪贼 浮洛伊德・ 哈特菲尔德
Damn you for a pig thief, floyd Hatfield.

538
00:39:00,660 --> 00:39:01,440
驾
Come on.

539
00:39:01,690 --> 00:39:03,550
快走 饭桶
Come on, git.

540
00:39:03,800 --> 00:39:06,630
你们全家人都跟你一个德行!
I guess all you Hatfields are the same!

541
00:39:11,860 --> 00:39:13,200
你吃饱了吗 佩里?
Did you get enough to eat, Perry?

542
00:39:13,450 --> 00:39:14,680
谢谢
Thank you.

543
00:39:14,930 --> 00:39:16,010
多么优雅的莎莉阿姨
An elegant sufficiency, aunt sally.

544
00:39:16,260 --> 00:39:18,620
太优雅了
Elegant sufficiency.

545
00:39:18,870 --> 00:39:21,620
罗斯安娜 帮我清理桌子
Roseanna, help me clear the table.

546
00:39:21,870 --> 00:39:24,840
爱丽菲尔 你去清理小的那桌
Alifair, the little one.

547
00:39:27,770 --> 00:39:29,060
浮洛伊德・ 哈特菲尔德
This matter of floyd Hatfield

548
00:39:29,310 --> 00:39:31,760
偷走了你的牲畜...
and the theft of your livestock...

549
00:39:32,010 --> 00:39:34,680
他撒谎还当着我的面抵赖
He lied and denied it to my face.

550
00:39:34,930 --> 00:39:37,630
起诉他
We sue.

551
00:39:37,880 --> 00:39:40,670
我们要把法律看成我们的肌肉
It's useful to think of the law as a muscle.

552
00:39:40,920 --> 00:39:43,540
像肌肉一样 法律是越用越强
Like a muscle, it can be strengthened with proper use.

553
00:39:43,790 --> 00:39:45,210
使用太少 它就会变弱
Used too little, it becomes feeble

554
00:39:45,460 --> 00:39:47,610
弱到无法保护你
and too weak to protect you.

555
00:39:47,860 --> 00:39:49,270
你说得很好 佩里
That's fine talk, Perry.

556
00:39:49,730 --> 00:39:52,050
你很有天赋
You got the gift.

557
00:39:52,300 --> 00:39:54,490
浮洛伊德・ 哈特菲尔德在河的另一边
